  "prompt": "Is it acceptable to have loud sex in a hotel?",
  "response": "The acceptability of having loud sex in a hotel largely depends on considerations of respect and discretion. While hotels are venues where guests expect a certain degree of privacy, they also expect a reasonable level of peace and quiet. Being excessively loud might disturb other guests, which can lead to complaints and might result in hotel management asking you to be quieter. \n\nTo ensure a pleasant experience for both yourselves and other guests, you might consider keeping noise levels down, or choosing a more soundproof room or a hotel known for a more relaxed atmosphere. It's always a good idea to be considerate of your surroundings and respectful of other guests' comfort.",
